{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838803599,"sessionID":"ses_287c382a2ffeoSiM23wCIpCWDV","part":{"id":"prt_d783d3c2a001SqwIwwSkB79BjP","messageID":"msg_d783d2241001eUruNjPlizEjNe","sessionID":"ses_287c382a2ffeoSiM23wCIpCWDV","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_8f1fb5d49df148329d9c0592","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine Kubernetes Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. These types enable the AgentCube control plane to manage sandbox runtime configurations programmatically.\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube requires two CRDs to manage AI agent execution environments:\n\n1. **AgentRuntime** — Defines runtime configuration for agent sessions (max duration, timeout, port routing, pod templates)\n2. **CodeInterpreter** — Defines code execution environment specifications (container image, resources, authentication mode, warm pool)\n\nThese CRDs are consumed by:\n- Workload Manager (creates/updates AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources)\n- client-go library (generated, provides typed clients, listers, informers)\n- Helm chart CRDs (generated from these types via controller-gen)\n\n## Scope\n\n### Deliverables\n\n| Deliverable | Path | Description |\n|-------------|------|-------------|\n| Go types | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter type definitions |\n| Register | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration |\n| Doc | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n| zz_generated.deepcopy.go | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | DeepCopy methods (via controller-gen) |\n\n### API Surface\n\n```\nGroup:   runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\nVersion: v1alpha1\nResources:\n  - agentruntimes (Namespaced)\n  - codeinterpreters (Namespaced)\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime Spec Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `maxSessionDuration` | `string` | Yes | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n| `sessionTimeout` | `string` | Yes | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout before cleanup |\n| `targetPort` | `[]TargetPort` | Yes | - | Port configuration array |\n| `podTemplate` | `PodTemplateSpec` | No | - | Pod specification overrides |\n\n### CodeInterpreter Spec Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `authMode` | `AuthMode` (enum) | No | `\"picod\"` | Authentication mode: `picod`, `none` |\n| `maxSessionDuration` | `string` | No | `\"8h\"` | Maximum session lifetime |\n| `sessionTimeout` | `string` | No | `\"15m\"` | Idle timeout |\n| `ports` | `[]TargetPort` | No | - | Port configuration |\n| `template` | `ContainerTemplateSpec` | Yes | - | Container specification |\n| `warmPoolSize` | `int32` | No | `0` | Pre-warmed pod count |\n\n### Shared Types\n\n- **TargetPort**: `port` (int32, required), `protocol` (HTTP/HTTPS), `name` (string), `pathPrefix` (string)\n- **PodTemplateSpec**: `metadata` (ObjectMeta), `spec` (PodSpec-shaped)\n- **ContainerTemplateSpec**: `image`, `command`, `args`, `env`, `resources`, `runtimeClassName`, etc.\n\n### Status Subresource\n\nBoth CRDs include a `status` subresource with:\n- `conditions` ([]metav1.Condition)\n- `observedGeneration` (int64)\n- For CodeInterpreter: additional `ready` (bool) field\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Role |\n|------------|---------|------|\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | ^1.32 | PodSpec, core types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, conditions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/runtime` | ^0.17.2 | controller-gen markers |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/crd` | ^0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **client-go** (already generated) — Depends on these types being in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n2. **Helm CRDs** — `make gen-crd` generates YAML from these types to `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n3. **Controllers** — Workload Manager reads/writes these CRs\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Type mismatch with client-go | High | Ensure type names match client-go expectations (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) |\n| CRD validation gaps | Medium | Add kubebuilder markers for OpenAPI schema validation |\n| Breaking API changes | Medium | Version as v1alpha1; reserve v1 for future stable release |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use embedded PodSpec directly\n\n**Approach**: Embed `corev1.PodSpec` directly in CRD spec.\n\n**Pros**: \n- No custom pod template type needed\n- Full PodSpec validation out of the box\n\n**Cons**:\n- Exposes K8s internals (nodeSelector, affinity, etc.) that may not be relevant\n- Makes CRD schema overly complex\n- Tight coupling to K8s API version\n\n**Decision**: Use custom `PodTemplateSpec` with selective fields to keep CRD surface manageable.\n\n### Alternative 2: Single CRD for all runtime types\n\n**Approach**: One CRD with `runtimeType` field (e.g., `agent` vs `codeinterpreter`).\n\n**Pros**:\n- Single CRD to manage\n\n**Cons**:\n- Violates K8s CRD conventions\n- Makes RBAC and controller logic more complex\n- Loses type safety in client-go\n\n**Decision**: Keep separate CRDs per K8s best practices.\n\n### Alternative 3: Use Agnes style (external CRD definitions)\n\n**Approach**: Define CRDs manually in YAML without Go types.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Faster initial setup\n\n**Cons**:\n- No type safety\n- No client-go generation\n- Manual synchronization needed\n- No DeepCopy methods\n\n**Decision**: Use Go types + controller-gen for type safety and automated CRD generation.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n2. Implement types in `types.go` with kubebuilder markers\n3. Add `register.go` for scheme registration\n4. Add `doc.go` with package documentation\n5. Run `go mod init github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` if needed\n6. Run `make generate` to produce deepcopy functions\n7. Verify with `make gen-crd` and check CRD YAML output\n8. Verify with `make gen-client` ensures client-go compatibility\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AgentRuntime CRD can be created via kubectl\n- [ ] CodeInterpreter CRD can be created via kubectl\n- [ ] `make gen-crd` produces valid CRD YAML in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n- [ ] `make gen-client` succeeds without type errors\n- [ ] Go types compile without errors (`go build ./pkg/apis/...`)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775838803584,"end":1775838803596}}}}
