ool) field\n72: \n73: ## Impact Analysis\n74: \n75: ### Dependencies\n76: \n77: | Dependency | Version | Role |\n78: |------------|---------|------|\n79: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | ^1.32 | PodSpec, core types |\n80: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, conditions |\n81: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object |\n82: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/runtime` | ^0.17.2 | controller-gen markers |\n83: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools/pkg/crd` | ^0.17.2 | CRD generation |\n84: \n85: ### Downstream Consumers\n86: \n87: 1. **client-go** (already generated) — Depends on these types being in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n88: 2. **Helm CRDs** — `make gen-crd` generates YAML from these types to `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n89: 3. **Controllers** — Workload Manager reads/writes these CRs\n90: \n91: ### Risks\n92: \n93: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n94: |------|----------|------------|\n95: | Type mismatch with client-go | High | Ensure type names match client-go expectations (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) |\n96: | CRD validation gaps | Medium | Add kubebuilder markers for OpenAPI schema validation |\n97: | Breaking API changes | Medium | Version as v1alpha1; reserve v1 for future stable release |\n98: \n99: ## Alternatives Considered\n100: \n101: ### Alternative 1: Use embedded PodSpec directly\n102: \n103: **Approach**: Embed `corev1.PodSpec` directly in CRD spec.\n104: \n105: **Pros**: \n106: - No custom pod template type needed\n107: - Full PodSpec validation out of the box\n108: \n109: **Cons**:\n110: - Exposes K8s internals (nodeSelector, affinity, etc.) that may not be relevant\n111: - Makes CRD schema overly complex\n112: - Tight coupling to K8s API version\n113: \n114: **Decision**: Use custom `PodTemplateSpec` with selective fields to keep CRD surface manageable.\n115: \n116: ### Alternative 2: Single CRD for all runtime types\n117: \n118: **Approach**: One CRD with `runtimeType` field (e.g., `agent` vs `codeinterpreter`).\n119: \n120: **Pros**:\n121: - Single CRD to manage\n122: \n123: **Cons**:\n124: - Violates K8s CRD conventions\n125: - Makes RBAC and controller logic more complex\n126: - Loses type safety in client-go\n127: \n128: **Decision**: Keep separate CRDs per K8s best practices.\n129: \n130: ### Alternative 3: Use Agnes style (external CRD definitions)\n131: \n132: **Approach**: Define CRDs manually in YAML without Go types.\n133: \n134: **Pros**:\n135: - Faster initial setup\n136: \n137: **Cons**:\n138: - No type safety\n139: - No client-go generation\n140: - Manual synchronization needed\n141: - No DeepCopy methods\n142: \n143: **Decision**: Use Go types + controller-gen for type safety and automated CRD generation.\n144: \n145: ## Implementation Plan\n146: \n147: 1. Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n148: 2. Implement types in `types.go` with kubebuilder markers\n149: 3. Add `register.go` for scheme registration\n150: 4. Add `doc.go` with package documentation\n151: 5. Run `go mod init github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` if needed\n152: 6. Run `make generate` to produce deepcopy functions\n153: 7. Verify with `make gen-crd` and check CRD YAML output\n154: 8. Verify with `make gen-client` ensures client-go compatibility\n155: \n156: ## Acceptance Criteria\n157: \n158: - [ ] AgentRuntime CRD can be created via kubectl\n159: - [ ] CodeInterpreter CRD can be created via kubectl\n160: - [ ] `make gen-crd` produces valid CRD YAML in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n161: - [ ] `make gen-client` succeeds without type errors\n162: - [ ] Go types compile without errors (`go build ./pkg/apis/...`)\n\n(End of file - total 162 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine Kubernetes Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module. These types enable the AgentCube control plane to manage sandbox runtime configurations programmatically.\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube requires two CRDs to manage AI agent execution environments:\n\n1. **AgentRuntime** — Defines runtime configuration for agent sessions (max duration, timeout, port routing, pod templates)\n2. **CodeInterpreter** — Defines code execution environment specifications (container image, resources, authentication mode, warm pool)\n\nThese CRDs are consumed by:\n- Workload Manager (creates/updates AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter resources)\n- client-go library (generated, provides typed clients, listers, informers)\n- Helm chart CRDs (generated from these types via controller-gen)\n\n## Scope\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775838808902,"end":1775838808915}}}}
